# React Native GitHub Actions

## Orchestrators

| Workflow | Role |
|----------|------|
| `rn.yml` | Main CI: `detect` → JS lint/security/test → **`expo-native-dirs`** gate (no-op for bare; for Expo asserts committed `android/` + `ios/`) → **`android-dev` / `ios-dev`** when `build_system` is **`bare`** or **`expo`** (PR: artifacts; push: Firebase). **`android-perf`:** after **`android-dev`** succeeds, downloads its APK artifact (no second Gradle build) and runs emulator perf gate (self-hosted Mac by default; see `rn-job-android-perf.yml`). **`detect`:** `expo` if `package.json` lists the **`expo`** package, else **`bare`**. No EAS jobs in this orchestrator. `pull_request` types still include `labeled` / `unlabeled` for other hooks. Other: `rn-internal-release.yml`, `rn-firebase-release.yml` |
| `rn-internal-release.yml` | Manual: **`auto` \| `bare` \| `expo`** (same `package.json` detection as `rn.yml`) → **`expo-native-dirs`** → Gradle + Fastlane for bare and Expo (committed native) |
| `rn-firebase-release.yml` | Manual Firebase: same **`build_system`** as `rn.yml`; **`expo-native-dirs`** then bare-style Firebase jobs; `platform` = `android-dist`, `android-dev`, etc. |
| `rn-code-health.yml` | Tech-debt / health scripts |
| `codeql-rn.yml` | CodeQL JavaScript |

## Reusable jobs (prefix `rn-job-`)

- **JS:** `rn-job-js-lint.yml`, `rn-job-js-test.yml`, `rn-job-security.yml`
- **Android:** `rn-job-android-build-bare.yml`, `rn-job-android-build-expo.yml`, `rn-job-android-internal-release-bare.yml`, `rn-job-android-internal-release-expo.yml`, `rn-job-android-debug-apk.yml`, `rn-job-android-firebase-release-bare.yml` (inputs `firebase_android_app` `dev`|`dist`, Gradle task + APK glob for flavor), `rn-job-android-perf.yml` (emulator perf gate; scripts in `scripts/perf/`, trend/baseline on `perf-data` branch)
- **iOS:** `rn-job-ios-build-bare.yml`, `rn-job-ios-build-expo-local.yml`, `rn-job-ios-build-expo-cloud.yml`, `rn-job-ios-internal-release-bare.yml`, `rn-job-ios-internal-release-expo.yml`, `rn-job-ios-firebase-release-bare.yml` — plus **optional** (not called from default `rn.yml`): `rn-job-ios-simulator-artifact.yml`, `rn-job-ios-test.yml`
- **EAS (not used by default `rn.yml`):** `rn-job-expo-eas-build-and-distribute.yml` — kept for manual or custom wiring

## Path rules

- Run Gradle with `working-directory: android` or `cd android`; cache key `android/**/*.gradle*`.
- Write `android/local.properties` with `sdk.dir=$ANDROID_HOME` after `setup-android`.
- iOS: `bundle exec pod install --project-directory=ios`; use the **workspace** under `ios/` produced by your app’s prebuild (bootstrap / Fastlane names vary by repo).
- **Xcode:** macOS iOS jobs pin **26.2** (Expo SDK 55 / EAS baseline). Do **not** override `DEVELOPER_DIR` to `/Applications/Xcode.app/...` when using `maxim-lobanov/setup-xcode`—that can mix toolchains and break Swift in `expo-modules-core`.
- Node **20** everywhere for JS and pre-Gradle steps.

## Workflow dispatch

`rn.yml` accepts `build_system` **`auto`** \| **`bare`** \| **`expo`**. **`auto`** maps to **`expo`** when `package.json` declares **`expo`**, else **`bare`**. Expo apps must **commit** `ios/` and `android/` after local **`expo prebuild`**; the **`expo-native-dirs`** job enforces presence. `package_manager` is reserved for future pass-through to install scripts.

`rn-firebase-release.yml` and `rn-internal-release.yml` use the same **`auto`** \| **`bare`** \| **`expo`** inputs and **`package.json`** detection; both run **`expo-native-dirs`** before native jobs.

## Reuse in another repository

See **`docs/RN_WORKFLOW_REUSE.md`** — `rsync` kit, `bootstrap_rn_workflow_ids.py`, `list_workflow_secrets.py`, and the one-shot prompt **`CURSOR_RN_DEVOPS_ONE_SHOT_APPLY.txt`**.
